manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: For APPLE CHARGER CORD Q1: Is this cable Apple mFi? A: The iPhone charger cable we sell is a MFi Lightning cable. You can log in to the official Apple MFi Accessories and search our brand "TUMABER" to confirm. Q2: Why does the phone get hot when it's charging? A: This is normal, because the phone will generate some heat when it is charging. However, the main reasons for the heat are as follows: 1. The charging speed will be faster when the phone power is low, the wall charger will output 9V high voltage, and the phone will generate heat because of the voltage converting process. 2. There are too many programs running in the background of the phone, causing the phone to run at a high load and generate more heat. Recommendations: 1. Clean up the running program of the phone with high power consumption in the background in time. 2. Don't play the phone while the phone is charged with low power, otherwise the phone will be in a high load state. About the error message "This accessory may not be supported by device": The message would appear if you were using a non-Apple wall charger or in poor transmission, but even if you are using an Apple accessory, the error can also happen for the firmware problem with iOS.

After analysis, the causes of this problem may be the following: Device lightning port contains impurities such as fiber and debris, resulting in poor transmission.The voltage of the wall charger is too low or unstable, resulting in insufficient power supply.The lightning end is corroded/stained, resulting in poor transmission.Circuit logic problems/system problems with charging equipment.The chip or mainboard of the cable is damaged. You can try the following solutions: You can use a pushpin to clean out the pocket lint or debris from the charging port.Wipe the Lightning end with a tissue to remove dirt and oxidation marks on the lightning end.Use the original charger or MFi charger, because some laptop USB output ports may have insufficient power output.

Upgarded C89 Apple MFi Connector Apple MFi ensures complete charge and sync compatibility with your Apple devices and new iOS system. Revolutionary Durability Bulletproof and durable nylon fiber cloth provides protection, strength and flexibility. It has been tested to withstand at least 12,000 cycles of 90 degree bend, which can be 12x durable than original device cables. The cable is made of high quality tinned copper and power cord, and covered with special insulation material to reduce the risk of short circuit.

Apple MFi Lightning Cable Enjoy lightning-fast data syncing and charging. MFi by Apple themselves to offer superior peace of mind. Use with any of your Apple devices with no safety or data concerns. reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Charging Made Convenient
reviews.reviewText: I've always been on the lookout for reliable and durable charging cables for my Apple devices, and this 3-pack of 6ft MFi Certified Charger Cables has been a fantastic find. Here's a breakdown of why they've become a staple in my tech arsenal:1. **Apple MFi Certified**: Knowing these cables are MFi certified gives me peace of mind. It means they're made to Apple's strict quality standards, ensuring a safe and efficient charge every time.2. **Extended Length**: The 6ft length is a game-changer. It offers that extra reach, whether I'm using my device on the couch, bed, or at a desk. No more being tethered too close to the power outlet.3. **Fast Charging**: With a 2.4A charging capability, my devices power up quickly. It's especially noticeable when I'm in a hurry and need a quick battery boost.4. **Durable Design**: These cables feel sturdy and well-made. They're not flimsy, and I've noticed they resist tangling, which is a huge plus for someone who often just tosses cables into a bag.5. **Value Pack**: Getting three cables in one pack is great value for money. I now have one for home, one for the office, and an extra for my travel bag.6. **Wide Compatibility**: These cables are compatible with a range of Apple devices, from the iPhone 13 all the way down to the iPhone 6. It's great knowing I can use them across multiple devices without any issues.In conclusion, this 3-pack of 6ft Apple MFi Certified Charger Cables is a solid investment for any Apple device owner. They're reliable, durable, and offer the convenience of fast charging and extended reach. Easily a 5-star product in my book! ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

I like the longer length for travelling because not every hotel has an outlet right next to the bed.I'm tough on my electronics- so I have worn a few of these out- which is where the 3 pack comes in handy. I'd say that these will last as long as any other standard charging cord I've owned. I should note that I use my phone when it's charging which likely adds to wear and tear.These get the job done!
